	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-07-17T04:12:15">Tate &amp; Lyle PLC provides ingredients and solutions to the food, beverage and other industries. The Company operates through two business segments: Speciality Food Ingredients, which offers products, such as sweeteners, texturants, health and wellness, and food systems, and Bulk Ingredients segment, which offers products, such as liquid sweeteners, industrial starches, citric acid, bio-fuels and animal feed. The Company operates a network of corn wet mills in the United States and Europe. In the United States, the Company's manufacturing assets include four corn wet mills, which are located in the Midwest, and one in Tennessee. Its other sites include SPLENDA Sucralose facility in McIntosh, Alabama, a citric acid plant in Ohio and a food systems blending facility in Illinois. In Europe, the Company's operations include five corn wet mills, including the Company's wholly owned plant in the Netherlands and four joint venture plants located in the Eastern European corn belt.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2016-02-19T07:19:56">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 September 2015, Tate &amp; Lyle PLC revenues decreased 2% to L1.18B. Net income before extraordinary items increased 29% to L67M. Revenues reflect Bulk  Ingredients segment decrease of 6% to L729M. Net income reflects Speciality Food  Ingredients segment income increase of 29% to L76M, Central Costs segment loss decrease of 28% to L18M. Dividend per share remained flat at L0.08.</Text>
	</TextInfo>
